OL,6,F"Patients who are already facing
OL,7,Flengthy waiting times should feel able
OL,8,Fto rely on the Health Board to manage
OL,9,Fthe waiting list well and in
OL,10,Faccordance with the waiting list
OL,11,Fguidelines.
OL,13,F"These three cases demonstrate clear
OL,14,Finjustice to the patients. In addition
OL,15,Fto these failings, the complainants
OL,16,Fhad the unnecessary stress and pain of
OL,17,Fpre-operative assessments.
OL,19,F"I am concerned that there appears to
OL,20,Fhave been no thought for the impact of
OL,21,Fthese on the patients' wellbeing."
